---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import { LEGAL_CONTACT, LEGAL_VERSIONS } from "../data/legal";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="CatPlay Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy information for the CatPlay website, waitlist and necessary storage."
>
  <Header currentPath="/privacy" />

  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container legal-shell">
      <span class="section-kicker">Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: April 26, 2026</p>
      <div class="legal-copy">
        <section>
          <h2>1. Controller</h2>
          <p>
            The controller for this website within the meaning of the GDPR is:
          </p>
          <p>
            {LEGAL_CONTACT.name}
            <br />
            {LEGAL_CONTACT.street}
            <br />
            {LEGAL_CONTACT.postalCode} {LEGAL_CONTACT.city}
            <br />
            {LEGAL_CONTACT.country}
            <br />
            Email: <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL_CONTACT.email}`}>{LEGAL_CONTACT.email}</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. What this website processes</h2>
          <p>
            When you visit this website, technical connection data can be processed to deliver the
            site securely and reliably. This may include the requested URL, date and time, IP
            address, referrer, browser information, device information, and server log data.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you join the waitlist, CatPlay processes your email address together with the
            consent text version, privacy policy version, timestamp, and request source in order to
            document and manage the waitlist request.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Hosting and service providers</h2>
          <p>
            This website is hosted on Vercel. Waitlist submissions are processed through Convex.
            Both providers act as technical service providers for the operation of the website and
            the waitlist workflow.
          </p>
          <p>
            The waitlist endpoint currently uses a Convex deployment in the EU West region
            (Ireland). Depending on the provider setup, support, security operations, or
            subprocessors, processing may still involve countries outside the EU/EEA. In those
            cases, transfers must rely on an appropriate legal transfer mechanism.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Waitlist emails</h2>
          <p>
            CatPlay uses the waitlist only to send product launch updates and early-access
            information related to CatPlay. The legal basis is your consent under Article 6(1)(a)
            GDPR. You can withdraw that consent at any time with effect for the future by emailing
            <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL_CONTACT.email}`}> {LEGAL_CONTACT.email}</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you withdraw your consent, your waitlist data will no longer be used for email
            updates and will be deleted unless retention is required for legal defense or another
            lawful reason.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Cookies and similar storage</h2>
          <p>
            CatPlay currently does not use analytics cookies, marketing cookies, or third-party
            tracking technologies on this website.
          </p>
          <p>
            The website only uses technically necessary storage and similar technologies where
            required for delivering the service you explicitly request. This includes a local
            storage entry named <code>catplay_privacy_preferences</code> to remember your privacy
            banner choice for up to 180 days.
          </p>
          <p>
            The legal basis for such technically necessary storage is Section 25(2) No. 2 TDDDG.
            Any related processing of personal data is based on Article 6(1)(f) GDPR, based on the
            legitimate interest in secure, stable, and user-friendly website operation.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Legal bases</h2>
          <p>The relevant legal bases for processing on this website are:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Article 6(1)(a) GDPR for waitlist communication based on your consent.</li>
            <li>
              Article 6(1)(f) GDPR for secure website delivery, abuse prevention, troubleshooting,
              and technical operation.
            </li>
            <li>
              Section 25(2) No. 2 TDDDG for technically necessary storage or access on your device.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Retention</h2>
          <p>
            Waitlist data is kept until one of the following happens: the waitlist purpose ends,
            you withdraw your consent, or the data is no longer required for the documented
            purpose.
          </p>
          <p>
            Technical log and operational data are retained only for as long as required for
            security, troubleshooting, and provider-side operational obligations.
          </p>
          <p>
            The local storage preference for the privacy banner is stored for up to 180 days and is
            then removed automatically when a new version is required or the stored expiry time has
            passed.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            Subject to the applicable legal requirements, you have the right to access, rectify,
            erase, restrict processing, object to processing, and data portability. Where
            processing is based on consent, you may withdraw your consent at any time with effect
            for the future.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Right to lodge a complaint</h2>
          <p>
            You have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. If the controller
            is based in Dresden, the competent authority is generally the Sächsische Datenschutz-
            und Transparenzbeauftragte, Maternistraße 17, 01067 Dresden,
            <a href="https://www.datenschutz.sachsen.de/" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">
              www.datenschutz.sachsen.de
            </a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Version of this notice</h2>
          <p>
            Privacy notice version: <code>{LEGAL_VERSIONS.privacyNotice}</code>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    min-height: 70vh;
    padding: 88px 0 120px;
    background: var(--cream-100);
  }

  .legal-shell {
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(42px, 6vw, 72px);
    line-height: 0.98;
    letter-spacing: -0.05em;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    color: rgba(28, 28, 30, 0.52);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .legal-copy {
    display: grid;
    gap: 28px;
    color: rgba(28, 28, 30, 0.74);
  }

  .legal-copy section {
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .legal-copy h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: #2d211a;
  }

  .legal-copy ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .legal-copy code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.95em;
  }

  .legal-copy a {
    color: var(--amber-700);
  }
</style>
